place.name: RUNHALL
place.gazetteerText: RUNHALL, a parish in Forehoe district, Norfolk; on the river Blackwater, 1 mile N by E of Hardingham r.station, and 5½ N W of Wymondham. Post-town, Wymondham. Acres, 834. Real property, £1, 626. Pop., 246. Houses, 51. The manor and most of the land belong to the Earl of Kimberley. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Coston, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £65. The church has a round tower. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
